who's come to gawk.

250
00:31:52,868 --> 00:31:55,928
They tolerate me for your sake.
- Of course.

251
00:31:56,706 --> 00:31:58,469
See? You think like them.

252
00:31:58,941 --> 00:32:01,569
Can't you see
I'm no longer with this crowd?

253
00:32:02,144 --> 00:32:03,543
I'm with you.

254
00:32:05,681 --> 00:32:07,444
You want me to swear?

255
00:32:09,085 --> 00:32:11,849
Yes, you're cute when you swear.

256
00:32:12,088 --> 00:32:14,852
You paid me a compliment!

257
00:32:19,695 --> 00:32:21,686
You know where the file
for 120 is?

258
00:32:21,864 --> 00:32:23,422
Find it for me.

259
00:32:24,266 --> 00:32:25,426
<i>Niccolo,</i>

260
00:32:31,741 --> 00:32:34,335
Excuse me, but we were first.

261
00:32:34,510 --> 00:32:36,273
Please be patient.

262
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:40,747
Who knows how long
the poor guy's been waiting.

263
00:32:41,150 --> 00:32:43,550
Well, he's not the only one.

264
00:32:44,887 --> 00:32:47,321
Did you get my message?
- Yes.

265
00:33:09,078 --> 00:33:11,706
- Something happened to my sister.
- An accident?

266
00:33:11,881 --> 00:33:14,543
No, they passed her over

267
00:33:14,717 --> 00:33:17,277
for head
of the gynecology department.

268
00:33:19,755 --> 00:33:21,382
It's an abuse of power.

269
00:33:24,026 --> 00:33:27,587
I'm sure it's my fault.
- What do you mean?

270
00:33:27,930 --> 00:33:30,421
He's starting to carry out
his threats.

271
00:33:32,468 --> 00:33:35,096
But the bastard
doesn't strike at me...

272
00:33:35,704 --> 00:33:37,467
but at someone close to me.

273
00:33:42,044 --> 00:33:43,636
That's a low blow.

274
00:34:07,136 --> 00:34:10,128
Do your parents have
any connections at the hospital?

275
00:34:10,306 --> 00:34:14,140
My mother might,
but you can't get her to do anything.

276
00:34:19,982 --> 00:34:21,279
What's wrong?

277
00:34:22,952 --> 00:34:25,648
- I'm really angry.
- Why?

278
00:34:25,821 --> 00:34:29,951
My mother's long-time lover
won't leave me alone.

279
00:34:30,793 --> 00:34:32,784
He keeps phoning,
asking to see me.

280
00:34:32,962 --> 00:34:34,987
Remember
that party at Dandini's

281
00:34:35,431 --> 00:34:38,366
when I stopped
to talk to a man?

282
00:34:39,935 --> 00:34:42,199
May I speak to you
for a moment?

283
00:34:43,539 --> 00:34:46,201
There's something I've wanted
to tell you for so long now.

284
00:34:46,375 --> 00:34:48,070
May I one of these days?

285
00:34:48,244 --> 00:34:49,871
Tell me now.

286
00:34:55,284 --> 00:34:57,650
You mean something
that happened 20 years ago?

287
00:34:57,820 --> 00:34:59,549
- How did you know?
- Intuition.

288
00:35:00,022 --> 00:35:02,684
Paternity
isn't an abstract concept.

289
00:35:02,858 --> 00:35:05,759
Your mother always said
if you just looked in the mirror,

290
00:35:06,395 --> 00:35:08,090
you'd know you were my daughter.

291
00:35:08,264 --> 00:35:10,755
I'd know no such thing.

292
00:35:11,567 --> 00:35:13,159
Look at our hands.

293
00:35:23,812 --> 00:35:26,406
I've hated him
ever since I was a child.

294
00:35:26,782 --> 00:35:29,342
But he's adored me
since the day I was born.

295
00:35:29,718 --> 00:35:32,653
But he could never tell anyone,
including me.

296
00:35:33,155 --> 00:35:36,386
He couldn't touch me,
caress me...

297
00:35:37,593 --> 00:35:40,994
because I always felt
an instinctive repulsion for him.

298
00:35:41,797 --> 00:35:46,029
I thought of him as a family friend.
I always avoided him.

299
00:35:47,169 --> 00:35:48,329
Why?

300
00:35:57,780 --> 00:35:59,475
It's not your fault.

301
00:36:02,384 --> 00:36:04,181
No, it's not, is it?

302
00:36:43,726 --> 00:36:45,557
See that girl?

303
00:36:45,861 --> 00:36:50,195
I was with a friend two days ago
when his motorcycle got a flat.

304
00:36:50,366 --> 00:36:55,099
A car was parked nearby.
I went over to borrow a screwdriver.

305
00:36:56,071 --> 00:36:59,973
She was inside,
totally naked, with a guy.

306
00:37:02,211 --> 00:37:03,178
You see?

307
00:37:03,345 --> 00:37:05,108
She recognizes me too.

308
00:39:50,446 --> 00:39:52,846
<i>Niccolo, don't forget the stamps,</i>

309
00:39:55,083 --> 00:39:57,711
<i>I may be crazy,</i>
<i>but I want to make a film with you,</i>

310
00:39:57,886 --> 00:40:01,845
<i>You'll have complete freedom,</i>
<i>I've sent the script over,</i>

311
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:21,237
Let's see if those
damned stamps are here.

312
00:40:25,180 --> 00:40:26,511
A catalogue.

313
00:40:35,958 --> 00:40:40,793
"Voices from the Other World,
or, Think - I Exist.

314
00:40:40,963 --> 00:40:43,796
Objective Proof
of Life After Death."

315
00:40:44,533 --> 00:40:47,229
"Complete freedom,"
and he sends me a script.

316
00:40:49,037 --> 00:40:52,165
"List of people who've communicated
with the other world."

317
00:40:52,341 --> 00:40:55,071
I almost feel like calling
one of them.

318
00:40:55,244 --> 00:40:57,439
Good Lord.

319
00:42:16,458 --> 00:42:18,949
- Would you cut it out?
- Who, me?

320
00:42:19,127 --> 00:42:20,788
You disappeared. What's up?

321
00:42:20,963 --> 00:42:24,057
If I don't put an end to this,
I won't get any work done.

322
00:42:24,499 --> 00:42:27,434
Think twice before stopping it.

323
00:42:28,070 --> 00:42:29,901
Is that why you came back?

324
00:42:31,740 --> 00:42:35,608
Who was it who said, " Family life
is an intrusion on one's private life"?

325
00:42:40,015 --> 00:42:43,815
I can't even think about myself,
or the film I want to make.

326
00:42:46,555 --> 00:42:48,250
What's this film about?

327
00:42:49,791 --> 00:42:51,816
I don't know the story yet.

328
00:42:51,994 --> 00:42:54,053
That's why I didn't tell you before.

329
00:42:54,496 --> 00:42:56,987
But the main character
is a woman.

330
00:42:57,165 --> 00:43:00,794
How can you know that
if you don't know the plot?

331
00:43:02,270 --> 00:43:03,897
It's a feeling.

332
00:43:05,374 --> 00:43:08,571
A feeling in female form.
It's hard to explain.

333
00:43:09,778 --> 00:43:12,303
- Another love story.
- I didn't say that.

334
00:43:12,614 --> 00:43:16,846
What possible meaning
can a love story have today

335
00:43:17,019 --> 00:43:21,422
with all the corruption
and decay around?

336
00:43:22,391 --> 00:43:25,918
Corruption is the cement
that holds this country together.

337
00:43:26,094 --> 00:43:29,586
Besides, corrupt people
are the first to want love stories.

338
00:43:32,968 --> 00:43:34,765
I'm looking for a face...

339
00:43:37,239 --> 00:43:40,640
an idea for the character,
but all I can think of is her.

340
00:43:46,381 --> 00:43:48,645
Won't she do for the character?

341
00:43:48,817 --> 00:43:53,083
Why the hell should Mavi be
in my film? She's in my life.

342
00:43:53,588 --> 00:43:55,055
Isn't it the same thing?

343
00:43:57,225 --> 00:44:00,422
Looking for a character means
looking for settings and a story line.

344
00:44:00,595 --> 00:44:02,324
And why can't you find them?

345
00:44:06,068 --> 00:44:07,763
Having a crisis, eh?

346
00:44:08,804 --> 00:44:09,702
What crisis?

347
00:44:15,310 --> 00:44:16,208
Listen...

348
00:44:17,779 --> 00:44:20,304
you and I have been
discussing things forever.

349
00:44:21,750 --> 00:44:26,744
We've examined and reexamined
so many theories and ideas.

350
00:44:26,922 --> 00:44:31,120
Meanwhile the world changes,
makes all our words out of date,

351
00:44:31,293 --> 00:44:33,284
and becomes increasingly
impenetrable.

352
00:44:35,997 --> 00:44:37,931
Have you ever gone hang gliding?

353
00:44:39,835 --> 00:44:41,769
Me neither,
but I can imagine it,

354
00:44:41,937 --> 00:44:45,532
and that's the sort of feeling
I'd like with a woman.

355
00:44:45,907 --> 00:44:49,399
But you always have to talk
and say something.

356
00:44:50,779 --> 00:44:52,610
Silence is oppressive.

357
00:44:55,851 --> 00:44:57,318
I'd like

358
00:44:57,486 --> 00:44:59,215
to be silent with a woman.

359
00:45:00,021 --> 00:45:05,084
Have the kind of relationship with her
that you have with nature.

360
00:45:10,832 --> 00:45:12,993
Unless you're crazy,

361
00:45:13,168 --> 00:45:16,069
what do you do
at the ocean or in the woods?

362
00:45:16,238 --> 00:45:18,103
You just look in silence.

363
00:45:18,874 --> 00:45:22,173
But though you don't realize it,
there's still a dialogue.

364
00:45:22,344 --> 00:45:25,074
You speak and you answer,

365
00:45:25,380 --> 00:45:27,473
as if it were another person.

366
00:45:27,983 --> 00:45:32,215
My ideal woman would be
like that other person.

367
00:45:32,654 --> 00:45:34,246
Ideal woman!

368
00:45:34,890 --> 00:45:37,950
Are you waiting for her?
- Yes, I am.

369
00:46:02,851 --> 00:46:06,617
Mavi, don't come over.
There's someone downstairs.

370
00:46:08,657 --> 00:46:11,057
<i>You hear?</i>
- What are you afraid of?

371
00:46:11,326 --> 00:46:13,521
I'm afraid for you, not me.

372
00:46:13,995 --> 00:46:17,453
Besides, it's not about fear.
- <i>You've lost your sense of humor,</i>

373
00:46:18,967 --> 00:46:20,992
That would be a shame.

374
00:46:21,770 --> 00:46:23,738
But maybe humor itself
has changed.

375
00:46:24,973 --> 00:46:26,668
Then I won't come over.

376
00:46:27,375 --> 00:46:28,842
Hold on.

377
00:46:35,917 --> 00:46:37,544
I'm not coming over.

378
00:47:31,072 --> 00:47:33,939
Look, I've got cellulite already.

379
00:47:34,342 --> 00:47:37,334
I should be
in the flower of my youth, but...

380
00:47:37,979 --> 00:47:40,607
<i>You'll be old when no one's</i>
<i>in love with you anymore,</i>

381
00:47:40,782 --> 00:47:43,876
<i>but I'm here now,</i>
<i>so don't worry,</i>

382
00:47:44,386 --> 00:47:46,854
Are you in love with me?

383
00:48:21,489 --> 00:48:23,047
Hello?

384
00:48:23,725 --> 00:48:26,592
I ran all the way up the stairs.

385
00:48:27,062 --> 00:48:31,431
No, I'd just gone out
for some cigarettes.

386
00:48:33,802 --> 00:48:37,260
How do I know
you're not seeing this man secretly?

387
00:48:37,439 --> 00:48:39,464
<i>I've told you so,</i>
<i>Want me to swear?</i>

388
00:48:39,641 --> 00:48:40,972
No, I believe you.

389
00:48:41,142 --> 00:48:43,133
<i>You say you do, but you don't,</i>

390
00:48:43,311 --> 00:48:45,472
Whatever you say.

391
00:48:45,947 --> 00:48:48,211
- Is that man still there?
- <i>Yes,</i>

392
00:48:48,516 --> 00:48:50,950
Invite him up for a drink.

393
00:48:51,119 --> 00:48:52,746
Good idea.

394
00:48:53,321 --> 00:48:55,687
I'll call you later.

395
00:51:34,082 --> 00:51:35,777
<i>My God! Who's there?</i>

396
00:51:35,950 --> 00:51:37,474
It's me.
Don't turn on the light.

397
00:51:37,652 --> 00:51:39,244
<i>You're crazy, Why not?</i>

398
00:51:39,420 --> 00:51:42,116
That guy at my place
followed me.

399
00:51:42,290 --> 00:51:46,021
If it's dark, he'll go away.
He must have a family too.

400
00:51:46,528 --> 00:51:49,429
Then you and I will go away.
- <i>Where to?</i>

401
00:51:49,597 --> 00:51:52,532
- The country, okay?
- Yes, my love.

402
00:51:53,101 --> 00:51:56,036
My love...

403
00:52:14,889 --> 00:52:17,824
Will it be cold?
Is the place heated?

404
00:52:17,992 --> 00:52:20,153
I don't know.
It's not my place.

405
00:52:20,328 --> 00:52:23,764
I rented it a few times
in the summer.

406
00:52:24,232 --> 00:52:27,633
It might be cold.
Bring a sweater or something.

407
00:53:00,635 --> 00:53:02,193
Look.

408
00:53:02,437 --> 00:53:04,200
Think that's him?

409
00:53:06,541 --> 00:53:08,441
No, that's not his car.

410
00:53:10,211 --> 00:53:13,578
Anyone out at night
must have their reasons,

411
00:53:13,748 --> 00:53:15,477
whether silly or serious.

412
00:53:15,650 --> 00:53:18,483
We think they're crooks.
You know why?

413
00:53:18,653 --> 00:53:22,783
We're the ones full of suspicion,
for purely emotional reasons.

414
00:53:48,383 --> 00:53:50,078
Here comes the fog.

415
00:53:50,351 --> 00:53:53,081
- Go slow.
- Slower than this?

416
00:53:54,122 --> 00:53:57,387
- I can't see.
- We just follow the white line.

417
00:54:09,637 --> 00:54:12,572
- Sure this is the right road?
- Let's hope so.

418
00:54:20,348 --> 00:54:22,441
Can I have a cigarette, please?

419
00:54:22,984 --> 00:54:24,315
Here.

420
00:54:25,887 --> 00:54:27,479
You got a light?

421
00:54:34,896 --> 00:54:37,023
I don't want it. You want it?

422
00:54:37,198 --> 00:54:38,631
Okay.

423
00:54:39,434 --> 00:54:41,095
Mad at me?

424
00:54:58,186 --> 00:55:00,984
A traffic light.
What's this about?

425
00:56:41,222 --> 00:56:42,655
Nick?

426
00:56:45,059 --> 00:56:46,526
Where are you?

427
00:56:48,229 --> 00:56:49,696
<i>I'm right here,</i>

428
00:56:55,136 --> 00:56:57,104
Don't disappear like that, please.

429
00:57:00,775 --> 00:57:03,403
Think we're being
spied on here too?

430
00:57:03,578 --> 00:57:05,045
I don't think so.

431
00:57:05,279 --> 00:57:07,042
I say we are.

432
00:57:11,886 --> 00:57:14,582
- Why do you say that?
- I feel it.

433
00:57:14,755 --> 00:57:18,623
Very well.
Want to bet we can shake them off?

434
00:57:39,547 --> 00:57:41,014
Watch out!

435
00:57:46,287 --> 00:57:48,517
You're crazy. Stop.

436
00:57:49,023 --> 00:57:50,388
I can't see a thing.

437
00:57:50,558 --> 00:57:52,651
I said stop!

438
00:57:54,729 --> 00:57:58,756
Please stop. I'm scared.

439
00:58:02,103 --> 00:58:03,468
Enough!

440
00:58:04,705 --> 00:58:06,605
I'm frightened! Stop!

441
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:20,451
Let me out.

442
00:58:46,147 --> 00:58:47,842
You're a real -

443
01:01:28,109 --> 01:01:29,576
Excuse me.

444
01:01:31,378 --> 01:01:34,836
Have you seen a girl
with short hair in a jacket?

445
01:01:35,015 --> 01:01:38,451
Who can see anything here?
There's a mess back there.

446
01:01:38,619 --> 01:01:42,248
I don't know what happened,
but shots were fired.

447
01:01:42,423 --> 01:01:44,118
Didn't you hear them?

448
01:01:45,326 --> 01:01:47,886
It seems
someone fell in the river.

449
01:01:48,496 --> 01:01:51,260
Seems there's a gang of...
- Hooligans.

450
01:01:51,432 --> 01:01:55,493
Stealing out of cars
and assaulting passengers.

451
01:01:55,703 --> 01:01:59,195
They even rang the bells.
- They sure did.

452
01:01:59,373 --> 01:02:01,034
Didn't you hear them?

453
01:02:01,208 --> 01:02:03,369
What about the ambulance?

454
01:02:04,078 --> 01:02:05,375
Are you deaf?

455
01:02:05,546 --> 01:02:08,174
I don't believe this.

456
01:03:00,701 --> 01:03:02,498
Don't you feel well?

457
01:03:40,474 --> 01:03:42,669
How long are you
gonna be mad at me?

458
01:04:17,278 --> 01:04:20,213
- It's all built on hollow ground.
- What?

459
01:04:21,248 --> 01:04:23,307
There's an old Roman villa
underneath.

460
01:04:23,484 --> 01:04:25,543
That's why they rented it to me.

461
01:04:25,719 --> 01:04:27,846
The house is sinking
into the void.

462
01:04:28,022 --> 01:04:30,490
Time exacts its revenge.

463
01:04:31,292 --> 01:04:33,726
Let's look.
I've never been down there.

464
01:04:46,240 --> 01:04:47,707
Give me your hand.

465
01:04:48,275 --> 01:04:49,742
Careful.

466
01:05:06,560 --> 01:05:08,027
Come on.

467
01:06:08,255 --> 01:06:09,882
It's damp.

468
01:06:13,093 --> 01:06:16,119
- It'll never light.
- Why so pessimistic?

469
01:06:16,864 --> 01:06:18,798
Don't you trust nature?

470
01:06:19,767 --> 01:06:21,530
In Baku, in Russia,

471
01:06:21,702 --> 01:06:24,000
there's still a temple
to the god of fire,

472
01:06:24,171 --> 01:06:28,801
with flames rising perpetually
from the bowels of the earth.

473
01:06:29,910 --> 01:06:31,969
It's actually
petroleum that's burning.

474
01:06:34,848 --> 01:06:38,045
They're swimming in it -
lucky them.

475
01:06:47,061 --> 01:06:50,827
- I'm fond of you.
- Why don't you say, "I love you"?

476
01:06:52,966 --> 01:06:55,298
I don't think
I've ever said it in my life.

477
01:06:57,671 --> 01:06:59,104
Too bashful, perhaps.

478
01:07:00,507 --> 01:07:02,338
Tell me you love me,

479
01:07:02,676 --> 01:07:05,338
and then tell me
what it means to love.

480
01:07:16,990 --> 01:07:18,719
You don't love me.

481
01:07:20,360 --> 01:07:23,454
You need me,
and that's not love.

482
01:07:26,667 --> 01:07:28,931
You need me in order to live

483
01:07:29,336 --> 01:07:30,894
or survive.

484
01:07:36,043 --> 01:07:39,535
That's everyone's problem today -
how to survive.

485
01:07:51,024 --> 01:07:52,321
I'm not wearing it.

486
01:07:52,493 --> 01:07:54,461
Why not?

487
01:07:55,362 --> 01:07:57,159
I like being cold.

488
01:07:58,465 --> 01:08:01,434
But you'd like to see me
wrapped in warm clothes

489
01:08:01,602 --> 01:08:04,230
so I don't catch pneumonia
or even a cold.

490
01:08:04,404 --> 01:08:07,464
Well, if I do, it's my business!

491
01:08:11,678 --> 01:08:13,737
You'll never catch anything.

492
01:08:13,914 --> 01:08:16,246
You're immune to disease,
like a shark.

493
01:08:16,416 --> 01:08:20,409
They can swallow a license plate
or the polio virus.

494
01:08:20,587 --> 01:08:22,418
They digest it all.

495
01:08:27,161 --> 01:08:29,061
I don't want to stay here.

496
01:08:36,170 --> 01:08:39,139
Where would we go?
There are no hotels around.

497
01:08:55,689 --> 01:08:57,884
And all those disgusting
creatures down there.

498
01:08:58,058 --> 01:09:00,549
It's sealed up.
Don't be afraid.

499
01:09:02,262 --> 01:09:04,093
You make me afraid.

500
01:09:05,566 --> 01:09:06,897
Me?

501
01:09:08,702 --> 01:09:11,193
I thought you felt
protected with me.

502
01:09:11,538 --> 01:09:13,802
