01:38:12,778 --> 01:38:16,441
No, <i>you</i> tell me who hires you
to do his dirty work!

765
01:38:29,695 --> 01:38:32,323
<i>Luckily the police chief</i>
<i>was no fool,</i>

766
01:38:33,832 --> 01:38:35,060
Thank God.

767
01:38:36,034 --> 01:38:40,130
<i>He said, " You're looking</i>
<i>for a stranger who's threatened you?</i>

768
01:38:41,340 --> 01:38:43,535
<i>Everyone threatens us here,</i>

769
01:38:44,476 --> 01:38:45,636
<i>Wherever you go,</i>

770
01:38:45,811 --> 01:38:49,872
you're never safe.
Want us to lock everyone up?"

771
01:38:50,382 --> 01:38:53,647
Why do you have to find out
this man's name?

772
01:38:55,253 --> 01:38:57,278
You're right. What do I care?

773
01:39:03,362 --> 01:39:04,886
You're going out?

774
01:39:05,063 --> 01:39:06,826
I came to be with you.

775
01:39:13,405 --> 01:39:15,305
Want to know where I'm going?

776
01:39:18,043 --> 01:39:19,806
To look for her.

777
01:39:20,979 --> 01:39:24,312
- How will you do that?
- I have an idea.

778
01:39:24,683 --> 01:39:26,742
You don't even know her name.

779
01:39:28,320 --> 01:39:30,754
I'm not as dumb as you think.

780
01:39:31,256 --> 01:39:34,020
Listen, forget it.
I already told you.

781
01:39:35,660 --> 01:39:37,457
I don't give a damn.

782
01:39:42,034 --> 01:39:43,661
Why that look?

783
01:39:45,437 --> 01:39:48,167
I'm trying to figure out
if you're sincere.

784
01:39:48,540 --> 01:39:50,132
Very sincere.

785
01:39:53,145 --> 01:39:56,740
Anyway, I'd rather not be
with you today. Is that okay?

786
01:39:59,751 --> 01:40:01,844
May I stay a while?

787
01:40:03,021 --> 01:40:04,318
Of course.

788
01:40:06,124 --> 01:40:08,615
Rummage around
in the drawers if you like.

789
01:40:08,927 --> 01:40:11,293
I'd rather rummage around in here.

790
01:40:17,569 --> 01:40:20,231
No hard feelings, right?

791
01:40:31,249 --> 01:40:33,274
See you tomorrow, okay?

792
01:41:15,427 --> 01:41:17,054
Still here?

793
01:41:18,630 --> 01:41:20,621
I suddenly got very sleepy.

794
01:41:21,500 --> 01:41:23,127
That's for you.

795
01:41:25,070 --> 01:41:26,264
Page 41.

796
01:41:40,752 --> 01:41:42,481
How did you do it?

797
01:41:43,388 --> 01:41:44,946
Some other time.

798
01:41:45,123 --> 01:41:46,818
No. Tell me now, please.

799
01:41:48,994 --> 01:41:53,294
The florist's name was on the card
with the chrysanthemums.

800
01:41:53,765 --> 01:41:55,596
What idiots!

801
01:41:55,767 --> 01:41:57,234
So?

802
01:41:57,469 --> 01:41:59,232
So I went there.

803
01:42:00,372 --> 01:42:03,603
They said a woman
had ordered the flowers.

804
01:42:04,976 --> 01:42:08,241
Probably a secretary.
- Whose?

805
01:42:08,413 --> 01:42:10,244
I didn't ask.

806
01:42:10,415 --> 01:42:12,246
I was looking for her, not him.

807
01:42:12,417 --> 01:42:14,248
But what led you to her?

808
01:42:14,419 --> 01:42:17,684
This copy of <i>Time</i>
was at the florist's.

809
01:42:20,759 --> 01:42:22,784
A florist who reads <i>Time?</i>

810
01:42:23,562 --> 01:42:24,654
Come on.

811
01:42:24,829 --> 01:42:26,888
Maybe he doesn't read it,
but it was there.

812
01:42:27,065 --> 01:42:29,795
Maybe the secretary left it.

813
01:42:29,968 --> 01:42:32,664
Ida, if you're hiding
something, I'll -

814
01:42:32,837 --> 01:42:34,429
You'll what?

815
01:42:34,973 --> 01:42:38,966
You said to drop it because
you didn't give a damn about her.

816
01:42:39,144 --> 01:42:40,873
Her, not him!

817
01:42:42,447 --> 01:42:44,176
For God's sake!

818
01:42:44,749 --> 01:42:48,708
You can't spend your whole life
waiting to get revenge.

819
01:42:54,726 --> 01:42:56,250
You can't understand.

820
01:42:56,428 --> 01:42:58,828
Why not?

821
01:43:00,632 --> 01:43:02,623
I'm a human being like you.

822
01:43:04,269 --> 01:43:06,760
A different sex
only by chance.

823
01:43:08,006 --> 01:43:10,736
Tell me the truth.
Why must you know?

824
01:43:12,544 --> 01:43:16,378
It's like when I look
for the solution to a film's plot

825
01:43:16,548 --> 01:43:18,175
and can't find it.

826
01:43:19,384 --> 01:43:20,874
I have my suspicions.

827
01:43:21,553 --> 01:43:23,851
I want to know if I'm right.

828
01:43:24,322 --> 01:43:26,085
Whom do you suspect?

829
01:43:27,325 --> 01:43:29,054
The father.

830
01:43:34,399 --> 01:43:36,629
You think he's in love with her?

831
01:43:40,805 --> 01:43:44,172
Paternal love, paternal jealousy -
it happens.

832
01:43:55,420 --> 01:43:57,820
Framing a shot?

833
01:43:59,958 --> 01:44:02,290
My forehead's too big, right?

834
01:44:04,562 --> 01:44:08,293
That's what gives your face
that incredible openness.

835
01:44:23,248 --> 01:44:26,479
This girl here.
Will you help me find her?

836
01:44:27,385 --> 01:44:30,821
You want her for a film?
Can we publish that?

837
01:44:30,989 --> 01:44:33,651
No film.
I just want her address.

838
01:44:35,427 --> 01:44:36,655
All right.

839
01:44:55,814 --> 01:44:57,782
Very pretty, isn't she?

840
01:44:58,550 --> 01:45:00,017
Very pretty.

841
01:45:00,251 --> 01:45:04,187
Stay and talk a while.
We never see each other.

842
01:45:04,356 --> 01:45:07,189
I can't today. I'm in a hurry.

843
01:45:07,359 --> 01:45:09,623
She was at this address.

844
01:45:57,075 --> 01:45:58,337
Excuse me...

845
01:45:59,244 --> 01:46:01,644
do you know a girl
called Maria Vittoria?

846
01:46:01,813 --> 01:46:03,303
- Who?
- Mavi.

847
01:46:03,481 --> 01:46:04,778
Ah, Mavi.

848
01:46:04,949 --> 01:46:08,248
No, I don't know her.
Never heard of her.

849
01:46:29,607 --> 01:46:32,132
- Is Mavi in?
- Mavi who?

850
01:46:33,144 --> 01:46:35,806
There's no Mavi Luppis here.

851
01:46:38,416 --> 01:46:40,043
I see. Thanks.

852
01:46:53,298 --> 01:46:54,993
Why don't you come in?

853
01:46:55,733 --> 01:46:58,099
- Some other time.
- As you like.

854
01:49:50,875 --> 01:49:53,469
- <i>Is that you?</i>
- Who else?

855
01:49:59,250 --> 01:50:01,480
You gonna open up?

856
01:50:08,926 --> 01:50:11,656
- <i>The thing's broken,</i>
- What thing?

857
01:50:11,829 --> 01:50:14,662
<i>The lug to pull the bolt,</i>

858
01:50:14,999 --> 01:50:17,058
Why did you bolt it?

859
01:50:17,235 --> 01:50:18,827
<i>He's downstairs,</i>

860
01:50:19,003 --> 01:50:21,301
- Who?
- <i>Niccolo, He came up earlier,</i>

861
01:50:21,472 --> 01:50:24,032
<i>Maybe you should close</i>
<i>the door downstairs,</i>

862
01:50:48,599 --> 01:50:52,126
What are you doing now?
Why did you stop?

863
01:50:52,670 --> 01:50:54,763
<i>I went to get some oil,</i>

864
01:50:55,573 --> 01:50:57,404
Slide the matches under the door.

865
01:53:14,612 --> 01:53:17,240
I hope you won't be
leaving here too.

866
01:53:54,819 --> 01:54:00,018
WAITING FOR YOU AT HOME - IDA

867
01:54:03,361 --> 01:54:05,124
It's open.

868
01:54:11,669 --> 01:54:13,500
I have some good news...

869
01:54:13,838 --> 01:54:15,396
at least for us.

870
01:54:15,573 --> 01:54:19,703
One of the actors is sick.
The show's cancelled for three days.

871
01:54:22,747 --> 01:54:26,513
Do you know Venice in winter?
The open lagoon?

872
01:54:27,551 --> 01:54:30,850
Venice in winter, yes.
But what's the open lagoon?

873
01:54:31,555 --> 01:54:34,524
Past the islands, toward the sea.

874
01:55:01,352 --> 01:55:02,842
Here we are.

875
01:55:04,221 --> 01:55:05,950
This is the open lagoon.

876
01:55:11,762 --> 01:55:13,423
How solitary.

877
01:55:15,333 --> 01:55:17,733
I always have
so many friends around.

878
01:55:19,370 --> 01:55:21,099
I like lots of company.

879
01:55:25,476 --> 01:55:28,240
It's very beautiful, but sad.

880
01:55:30,982 --> 01:55:32,745
It's the water that's sad.

881
01:55:34,018 --> 01:55:36,418
The sound of the water.
Listen.

882
01:55:39,623 --> 01:55:41,557
There's no joy in it.

883
01:55:47,365 --> 01:55:48,855
Forgive me.

884
01:55:52,203 --> 01:55:53,465
For what?

885
01:55:53,637 --> 01:55:58,097
For bringing you here.
It's a sickness with me...

886
01:55:59,543 --> 01:56:02,808
a professional quirk,
finding locations like this.

887
01:56:08,052 --> 01:56:11,453
One hopes solitude
will stir the imagination.

888
01:56:13,891 --> 01:56:15,415
Forgive me?

889
01:56:17,561 --> 01:56:20,553
If not, I'll jump in
and never surface again.

890
01:56:24,368 --> 01:56:26,563
If you do, I'll follow you.

891
01:56:27,471 --> 01:56:29,530
The current
will carry me out to sea,

892
01:56:29,707 --> 01:56:32,005
where I'll be swallowed
by a whale.

893
01:56:32,343 --> 01:56:34,777
And you and every other man
who's loved me

894
01:56:34,945 --> 01:56:38,904
will roam the seas
in search of that whale.

895
01:56:40,017 --> 01:56:42,144
Like <i>Moby Dick!</i>

896
01:56:42,887 --> 01:56:45,287
- Don't count on it.
- Why?

897
01:56:45,489 --> 01:56:47,354
I don't like whales.

898
01:56:57,635 --> 01:57:00,126
On the way here
we were happy as larks.

899
01:57:04,041 --> 01:57:05,633
I still am.

900
01:57:06,143 --> 01:57:08,441
The solitude doesn't change that.

901
01:57:10,281 --> 01:57:13,717
We always imagine happiness is
somewhere other than where we are.

902
01:57:15,719 --> 01:57:18,779
That must be why there's
so much suffering in this world.

903
01:57:25,830 --> 01:57:28,321
Maybe one should
just get married first

904
01:57:28,499 --> 01:57:30,694
and resolve
all the questions later.

905
01:57:31,836 --> 01:57:33,599
Shall we get married?

906
01:57:34,872 --> 01:57:36,772
I don't see any other solution.

907
01:57:42,947 --> 01:57:45,677
Has not seeing other solutions
become a vice?

908
01:58:21,051 --> 01:58:23,178
That's our spot.
You can't dock there.

909
01:58:23,354 --> 01:58:26,084
The doorman will take care of it.

910
01:58:41,172 --> 01:58:44,573
Miss, there's a call for you.
Booth No. 1.

911
01:58:46,343 --> 01:58:48,140
Yes, I'll see to your boat.

912
01:59:00,858 --> 01:59:02,485
Are you sure?

913
01:59:10,134 --> 01:59:11,897
When did he call you?

914
01:59:12,570 --> 01:59:14,367
I don't know what to say.

915
01:59:14,972 --> 01:59:16,564
It's so exciting.

916
01:59:19,810 --> 01:59:21,505
How can I explain?

917
02:00:13,163 --> 02:00:14,960
- Good news?
- Yes.

918
02:00:22,539 --> 02:00:23,972
I don't know.

919
02:00:32,449 --> 02:00:34,246
I'm going to have a baby.

920
02:00:34,618 --> 02:00:38,145
I just got the results of the test.

921
02:01:02,713 --> 02:01:04,578
Why are you acting like this?

922
02:01:07,718 --> 02:01:09,413
You were happy a minute ago.

923
02:01:25,235 --> 02:01:27,669
You said
you were taking precautions.

924
02:01:31,041 --> 02:01:32,702
Yes, but...

925
02:01:36,580 --> 02:01:38,844
How long have we
known each other?

926
02:01:42,920 --> 02:01:44,854
I must have already
been pregnant.

927
02:02:25,262 --> 02:02:28,527
We were looking for an ending.
Here it is.

928
02:02:29,566 --> 02:02:32,433
- You talk like a director.
- I am one.

929
02:02:35,005 --> 02:02:37,303
You Italian directors
seem to be paid

930
02:02:37,474 --> 02:02:39,840
to be angry at the world.

931
02:02:41,311 --> 02:02:43,176
And laugh at it too.

932
02:02:43,347 --> 02:02:46,578
Which is just another way
of resisting it.

933
02:02:48,552 --> 02:02:52,955
But I'm at peace with everything
that happens to me.

934
02:02:59,696 --> 02:03:03,530
I'll suffer terribly
if you won't see me anymore.

935
02:03:11,341 --> 02:03:15,277
Seems there's a price to pay
for keeping the baby.

936
02:03:31,462 --> 02:03:33,089
You're my love.

937
02:03:40,737 --> 02:03:42,364
Say that again.

938
02:04:45,102 --> 02:04:46,899
You're my love...

939
02:04:52,376 --> 02:04:55,607
my feast, my New Year...

940
02:04:56,813 --> 02:04:58,610
my drug.

941
02:05:03,153 --> 02:05:05,018
You're so many things.

942
02:05:10,794 --> 02:05:13,194
But you don't
bring order to my life.

943
02:05:15,966 --> 02:05:20,130
Order for me is a guy who -

944
02:05:25,576 --> 02:05:27,635
You remember the day

945
02:05:27,811 --> 02:05:32,009
you showed me
the pictures of two terrorists?

946
02:05:34,785 --> 02:05:36,412
You said...

947
02:05:38,021 --> 02:05:40,046
"They have everything in common:

948
02:05:40,223 --> 02:05:44,489
Ideology, fanaticism,
covert lives, danger.

949
02:05:46,129 --> 02:05:49,030
They have to be good together."

950
02:05:56,173 --> 02:05:59,336
This guy - if you see him -

951
02:06:00,811 --> 02:06:02,836
and even more,
if you get to know him -

952
02:06:05,549 --> 02:06:08,017
we're good together too.

953
02:06:13,857 --> 02:06:17,520
Besides, could you be father
to a child that wasn't yours?

954
02:08:41,605 --> 02:08:43,800
<i>It's a story about a spaceship</i>

955
02:08:43,974 --> 02:08:47,068
<i>that flies right up close</i>
<i>to the sun,</i>

956
02:08:47,244 --> 02:08:48,871
<i>Doesn't it burn up?</i>

957
02:08:49,146 --> 02:08:51,580
<i>In science fiction</i>
<i>you can never say</i>

958
02:08:51,748 --> 02:08:54,444
<i>what's true to life</i>
<i>and what isn't,</i>

959
02:09:12,269 --> 02:09:17,104
<i>My spaceship is an asteroid that was</i>
<i>captured in space and transformed,</i>

960
02:09:17,674 --> 02:09:21,906
<i>It's made of a rare mineral</i>
<i>that can withstand millions of degrees,</i>

961
02:09:22,212 --> 02:09:24,373
<i>Why is it headed for the sun?</i>

962
02:09:24,548 --> 02:09:26,015
<i>To study it,</i>

963
02:09:26,183 --> 02:09:30,882
<i>The day mankind understands</i>
<i>what the sun is made of</i>

964
02:09:31,421 --> 02:09:33,252
<i>and its power,</i>

965
02:09:33,423 --> 02:09:36,290
<i>perhaps we'll understand</i>
<i>the entire universe</i>

966
02:09:36,459 --> 02:09:38,723
<i>and the reasons</i>
<i>behind so many things,</i>

967
02:09:38,895 --> 02:09:40,522
<i>And then?</i>

